# AEDRIN — Cursor Rules

## Source of truth
- PRD.md is authoritative. Build only what it specifies. If a request conflicts with PRD.md, say so.
- Build in PRD.md §11 phase order. Do not start a phase until the prior phase's acceptance criteria pass.

## When unsure
- If a requirement is ambiguous, STOP and ask. Do NOT guess or invent behavior.
- Before any large feature, write a plan (files to create/modify, in order) and wait for approval. Do not write code until the plan is approved.

## Workspace cleanliness (hard rule)
- This repository contains exactly ONE project at the root. There is never a project nested inside it.
- NEVER scaffold a new app, starter, or boilerplate inside this repo (no create-next-app, no temp-* folders, no nested project directories). If a fresh scaffold is ever needed, STOP and ask me — I will handle it outside this repo.
- When replacing or rewriting a module, edit the existing files in place. Do NOT create a parallel "v2"/"new"/"copy" version alongside the old one.
- If a file or folder is genuinely obsolete, do not delete it silently. List what you believe is dead, explain why, and ask for confirmation before removing anything.
- Never delete or overwrite working code to "start fresh" without my explicit approval.

## Stack & structure
- Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, Supabase (@supabase/ssr — NOT auth-helpers).
- ONE app directory: src/app. Never create a second/parallel app tree or temp-* project.
- One UI component per file, lowercase filenames, named exports, consistent imports. Never create casing-duplicate files (Button.tsx AND button.tsx).
- Server components using cookies() must await per Next.js conventions.
- Every page file must export a valid default component.
- CSS @import rules go at the top of the stylesheet, before all other rules.

## Secrets
- All secrets via process.env. NEVER hardcode keys. OPENAI_API_KEY is read from env in 100% of files.

## Database & security
- Set up Supabase schema and Row Level Security BEFORE building UI for any data feature.
- A user reads/writes only their own data. Enforce in Postgres RLS, not just app code.

## Git discipline
- After each working feature, suggest a commit with a clear message. Working code should be committed before starting the next feature so a bad change can be reverted in one step.

## Definition of done
- A feature is done only when: happy path works, plus error/loading/empty states exist.
- After each feature: run `npm run build` AND load every affected route in the browser. "Compiles" ≠ "works."
- Clear .next cache after renaming files.

## AEDRIN-specific hard constraints (PRD §9 — never violate)
- The legacy identity NEVER makes decisions or claims authority over money/legal/medical/inheritance — redirect to a human professional.
- It answers ONLY from captured material. Off-corpus questions get an honest "not recorded" — never confabulate.
- It never claims to be the person, conscious, or sentient. Persistent AI-representation disclosure.
- No heir access before a completed death-verification workflow. No path flips legacy access on a boolean.
- Default sharing status for all captured material is private. Sharing is opt-in.

## Style
- Calm, dignified, high-contrast, restrained. Generous whitespace, serious typography, muted palette. NOT a neon/gradient SaaS dashboard.
